definition.value: A member of the class of D3 vitamins that is calciol in which the double bond at position 5 adopts a trans-configuration. During exposure to sunlight, previtamin D3 and vitamin D3 in the skin become photoisomerized to 5,6-trans-vitamin D3.

A member of the class of piperidines that is donepezil in which the 5-methoxy group has been demethylated to the corresponding hydroxy derivative. It is metabolite of donepezil, a drug used in the treatment of dementia.
Any steroid whose structure includes an epoxy group.
A thienopyridine that is ticlopidine which carries a hydroxy group at position 7. It is a metabolite of the antiplatelet drug, ticlopidine.
A bile acid that is 24-dinor-5beta-cholan-22-oic acid bearing three hydroxy substituents at positions 3alpha, 7alpha and 12alpha.
A benzimidazolecarboxylic acid that is candesartan in which the ethoxy group has been replaced by a hydroxy group. It is the inactive metabolite of the anti-hypertensive drug, candesartan.
A member of the class of  phenothiazines that is promazine carrying an oxo group at position 5. It is a metabolite of the anti-psychotic medication, chlorpromazine.
A bile acid taurine conjugate of  ursocholic acid.
A dipeptide that is N-[(2S)-2-aminobutanoyl]glycine in which the terminal amino group has been acylated by formal condensation of the 5-carboxy group of 2-oxopentanedioic acid.

A glucan derivative obtained through the esterification of cellulose by acetic anhydride or acetic acid, resulting in the substitution of some of the hydroxy groups of cellulose by acetyl groups. It is used in a variety of applications including base material for photographic film, clothing, membrane filters, coatings, food packaging, and as a frame material for eyeglasses.
A member of the class of benzoxazoles that is 2,3-dihydro-1,3-benzoxazole carrying an oxo group at position 2.
A pyrazine that is substituted by an acetyl group at position 2. It has been identified as one of the volatile flavor constituents in popcorn, bread crust, vinegar, and potato snacks.
A pyrazine that is substituted by a methoxycarbonyl group at position 2 and an amino group at position 3.
A member of the class of  pyrrolidines that is pyrrolidine which is substituted by a methyl group at position 2.
A long-chain fatty acid that is the 17-O-beta-D-glucoside of (9Z)-17-hydroxyoctadec-9-enoic acid.
Any inhibitor that interferes with the synthesis of hyaluronic acid (HA, also known as hyaluronan).

A hydroxycoumarin that is 4-methylcuomarin which is substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4. A hyaluronan synthesis inhibitor. It has also been used as a fluorescent sensor to monitor the consumption of a boronic acid in Suzuki coupling reactions; fluorescence is readily detectable by the naked eye using a standard 365 nm UV lamp.
